				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Cool poem! I don&#8217;t know much about poetry, so I can&#8217;t tell you how well it works in general, but I enjoyed it. It&#8217;s about telling bedtime fantasy stories, and following in the traditions of those tales.</p>
<p>The only thing that I wondered about in the poem was the punctuation at the end of the sentences. Seemed as tough some might be missing, but then if I ever do read a poem I wonder about the punctuation 😛</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/08/05/an-introduction-to-a-dream/?replytocom=379#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "div-comment-379", "379", "respond", "178" )' aria-label='Reply to Rudy Neeser'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
